text: Huntington is a city in Cabell County and Wayne County in the U.S. state of West Virginia. It is the county seat of Cabell County. Huntington is the second largest city in West Virginia, with a population of 46,842 at the 2020 census. It is one of the central cities of the Huntingtonâ€“Ashland metropolitan area.
